The paper discusses a distributed framework for building service-based systems, which suggests that it could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The framework also includes AI algorithms, which could place it under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also mentions the use of REST, HTTP, and Web Services, which are common in Software Engineering (cs.SE). The system is mobile-compatible with Android, which could suggest the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Finally, the paper focuses on the autonomic setup and linking mechanism, which could place it under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
